  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The addition of the RBAC settings to `pkg/genericapiserver/options` added a dependency from that code to pkg/apiserver (and also coupled pkg/apiserver to the registry implementations of security).  /options needs to not depend on low level code details so it can be imported from external code and used to do validations.  \n\nA couple of changes need to be made:\n1. The flags in `pkg/genericapiserver/options` related to authorization need to be defined in a package that does not import the full RBAC code tree\n2. `pkg/apiserver/authz.go` needs to be split up into its own package - `pkg/apiserver` will likely be moved out of our codebase and can't take dependencies on specific Authz implementations.  The code that initializes the authorizer probably belongs in `pkg/genericapiserver/authorization`, and should only be imported by `cmd/kube-apiserver/app`.\n\nIn general we don't want our generic code packages to know the details of what lies behind the authorizer interface.\n\nAssigning to @ericchiang for now, but this will block extracting the core API server machinery code into a library.\n",
